data.meta_description:
11 likes, 2 comments - jamescbgray on May 3, 2024: "On this date May 3rd in the year 1933 James Brown was born in Barnwell,South Carolina and moved to Augusta,Georgia with family when he was 4 years old.James Brown is one of the founding fathers of funk music and a major figure of popular music and dance.He is often referred to as "the Godfather of Soul" or "the Hardest Working Man in Show business"

 In a career that spanned six decades,Brown profoundly influenced the development of many different music genres.James Brown holds the record as the artist with the most singles on the billboard hot 100 charts,Brown recorded 17 number one singles on the R&B charts.

Brown was honored by many institutions,including inductions into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame and the Song Writers Hall of Fame.Brown is also ranked 7th on Rolling Stone Magazine's list of 100 greatest artists of all times.
